[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Personal Current Account Manifesto for NI
[normal] 
[normal]( See appendix A)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]• 
[normal]All consumers should be able to open a bank account unless they have a
[normal] 
[normal]criminal conviction
[normal] that prevents them from doing s
[normal]o.
[normal]• Branches should have opening hours to suit consumers and provide a full
[normal] 
[normal]range of services.
[normal]• Staff should be involved in training programmes to deal with every
[normal] 
[normal]eventuality and 
[normal]be empowered to make decisions to help consumers quickly.
[normal]• Fees and charges should be transparent, fair and proportionate.
[normal]• Better communication around how consumers are protected online and training to use these services are vital.
[normal]• Contacting the bank should cost the same for new and existing
[normal] 
[normal]customers. More detail is needed on how much it costs to call using
[normal] 
[normal]different networks.
[normal]• Communications should be in plain English. More work is needed to 
[normal]revise how 
[normal]changes to products can be more easily communicated whilst remaining within the guidelines from the financial regulator.
[normal]• Product offerings should be presented in a way that helps consumers compare the full range of services and know that they can switch.
[normal]• The complaints process should be available from all points of contact,
[normal] 
[normal]verbal 
[normal]complaints logged and actioned and leaflets available in branch displays.
[normal]• A review of packaged accounts, eligibility processes and usage of
[normal] 
[normal]individual 
[normal]services is needed.
